---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Textiles — Fabric Terms That Score Big"
  description="Fabric and textile words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. CHINTZ (20pts), KHAKI (16pts), TWEED (9pts), DENIM (8pts). Textile vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble textile words, fabric scrabble terms, chintz scrabble points, khaki scrabble, tweed scrabble word, denim scrabble, textile words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Textiles — Fabric Terms That Score Big","description":"Fabric and textile words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. CHINTZ (20pts), KHAKI (16pts), TWEED (9pts), DENIM (8pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-textiles"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is CHINTZ a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! CHINTZ scores 20 points (C=3, H=4, I=1, N=1, T=1, Z=10). It's a printed cotton fabric with a glazed finish, valid in both TWL and SOWPODS. The Z tile contributes half the total score."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is KHAKI worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"KHAKI scores 16 points (K=5, H=4, A=1, K=5, I=1). It uses both K tiles from the bag and the H tile, making it a powerful consonant-clearing word. It means a brownish-yellow fabric used for military uniforms."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is TWEED valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. TWEED scores 9 points (T=1, W=4, E=1, E=1, D=2) and refers to a rough woollen cloth. While not the highest scorer, it's useful for clearing the W tile with common letters."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Textiles — Fabric Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Textile and fabric words are underrated in Scrabble. Many come from foreign languages — Hindi, French, Scottish — and carry unusual letter combinations that score surprisingly well. CHINTZ alone delivers 20 points with its Z tile, while KHAKI burns both K tiles in one go.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">20 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CHINTZ (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">16 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">KHAKI</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWEED</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DENIM</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">High-Scoring Fabric Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">CHINTZ — 20 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">C=3, H=4, I=1, N=1, T=1, Z=10 · 6 letters · Z tile powerhouse</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A printed cotton fabric with a glazed finish. CHINTZ is one of the best Z words in Scrabble — 6 letters, 20 points base score, and it uses the Z with otherwise common letters (C, H, I, N, T). On a double or triple word square, this becomes devastating.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧵 KHAKI</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">16 pts · K=5, H=4, A=1, K=5, I=1 · Brownish-yellow fabric</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🪡 VOILE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · V=4, O=1, I=1, L=1, E=1 · Sheer fabric</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧶 TWEED</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · T=1, W=4, E=1, E=1, D=2 · Rough woollen cloth</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">👖 DENIM</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · D=2, E=1, N=1, I=1, M=3 · Sturdy cotton fabric</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Textile Words for Your Arsenal</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SILK</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">GAUZE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FELT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CREPE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BATIK</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">LINEN</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Textile Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CHINTZ is your best Z play under 7 letters:</span> At 20 points from 6 tiles (3.3 per tile), CHINTZ outscores most Z words. The surrounding letters (C, H, I, N, T) are all common, so you'll often have them when you draw the Z.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">KHAKI uses both K tiles:</span> There's only one K tile in the bag, so KHAKI requires a blank for the second K — or wait until you draw it naturally. But when it works, 16 points from 5 tiles is excellent rack clearance.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">GAUZE for the Z without consonants:</span> If you have the Z but lack consonants, GAUZE (15pts) uses mostly vowels around it. G=2, A=1, U=1, Z=10, E=1 — only one consonant needed.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Textile words are <span class="text-white font-medium">Z and K specialists</span>. CHINTZ, GAUZE, and KHAKI give you reliable plays for two of Scrabble's trickiest high-value tiles. Memorise these three and you'll never be stuck with Z or K on your rack again.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid textile word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-700 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-astronomy/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Astronomy</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-aviation/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Aviation</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-camping/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Camping</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-carpentry/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Carpentry</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-ceramics/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Ceramics</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
